params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Required. The group whose members are listed. The format is: projects/[PROJECT_ID_OR_NUMBER]/groups/[GROUP_ID]

params.name: data.page_size
params.description: A positive number that is the maximum number of results to return.

params.name: data.page_token
params.description: If this field is not empty then it must contain the next_page_token value returned by a previous call to this method. Using this field causes the method to return additional results from the previous method call.

params.name: data.filter
params.description: An optional list filter describing the members to be returned. The filter may reference the type, labels, and metadata of monitored resources that comprise the group. For example, to return only resources representing Compute Engine VM instances, use this filter: resource.type = "gce_instance"

params.name: data.interval
params.description: An optional time interval for which results should be returned. Only members that were part of the group during the specified interval are included in the response. If no interval is provided then the group membership over the last minute is returned.
